Third-party code included in this distribution
===============================================

1. hyworld2/ (vendored Python package)
---------------------------------------
Location in this repo:  hyworld2/
Source:                 https://github.com/filliptm/HY-World-2.0-Playground
License:                MIT (Copyright (c) 2026 filliptm)

The `hyworld2/` directory is a verbatim copy of the Python package from the
Playground fork above, with two local modifications documented inline:

  - hyworld2/worldrecon/hyworldmirror/utils/save_utils.py
        Stores the opacity field as logit (pre-sigmoid) in the output PLY
        so the file round-trips correctly through any standard 3D Gaussian
        Splatting viewer, including LichtFeld Studio's own loader. Upstream
        stored it post-sigmoid, which double-sigmoids on reload.

  - hyworld2/worldrecon/hyworldmirror/utils/visual_util.py
        Trimmed to the three functions the inference path actually uses
        (segment_sky, run_skyseg, download_file_from_url). Dropped the
        GLB-mesh / gradio-viewer code and the matplotlib / trimesh /
        scipy / requests imports that went with it.

Also dropped from the vendored copy:
  - hyworld2/worldrecon/gradio_app.py  (web UI, not used by the plugin)


2. Model weights (downloaded at runtime, NOT redistributed)
-----------------------------------------------------------
On first Run, the plugin downloads these into <plugin>/models/:

  - tencent/HY-World-2.0 (subfolder: HY-WorldMirror-2.0) — ~4.8 GB
        License:  Tencent HY-WORLD 2.0 Community License Agreement
        Source:   https://huggingface.co/tencent/HY-World-2.0
        Note:     Geographically restricted per the license terms.

  - JianyuanWang/skyseg (skyseg.onnx) — 168 MB
        Source:   https://huggingface.co/JianyuanWang/skyseg

Users acquire these weights directly from HuggingFace under their respective
licenses. The plugin itself does not bundle, mirror, or redistribute any
model weights.


